cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and deep learning (DL) techniques for predicting surface normals from a single image. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new CNN architecture for this task, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of constraints and intermediate representations, which are common techniques in the field of deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well. Furthermore, the paper deals with 3D scene understanding, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO), making them possible sub-categories as well.
